# Shared Module Usage Priority Standards

> **Related Rules**: See [Angular 20 Best Practices](./angular.mdc), [Shared Module Specific Standards](./shared-specific.mdc)

## Basic Principles

- All UI layer components must prioritize using `SHARED_IMPORTS`
- Prohibit fragmented imports of Angular, ng-zorro-antd, @delon modules
- Only import individually when `SHARED_IMPORTS` cannot meet requirements
- Maintain consistency and maintainability of module imports

## Usage

```typescript
import { SHARED_IMPORTS } from '@shared';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-example',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [SHARED_IMPORTS], // Prioritize using SHARED_IMPORTS
  // ...
})
export class ExampleComponent {}
```

- Import `SHARED_IMPORTS` from `src/app/shared/shared-imports.ts`
- Use `SHARED_IMPORTS` in the component's `imports` array
- Refer to `docs/45-SHARED_IMPORTS-使用指南.md` for complete usage

## Exception Cases

- Only import individually when `SHARED_IMPORTS` truly cannot meet requirements
- Must document the reason in code when importing individually

